      "term": "nondisjunctions",
      "kind": "word",
      "cefrLevel": "null",
      "senses": [
        {
          "pos": "noun",
          "definition": "plural of nondisjunction, the failure of paired chromosomes to separate properly during cell division",
          "examples": [
            "Nondisjunctions can lead to an abnormal number of chromosomes in daughter cells.",
            "Researchers study nondisjunction events to understand certain genetic disorders."
